<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id05f200e1-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s2577"><num value="2577">§ 2577.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding <ref href="/us/usc/t19/s2571">section 2571 of this title</ref>, for purposes of this part—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id05f200e2-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s2577/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> NAFTA</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “NAFTA” means the North American Free Trade Agreement.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id05f200e3-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s2577/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> State</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The term “State” means any of the several States, the District of Columbia, and the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id05f200e4-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/39/tIV/s481">Pub. L. 96–39, title IV, § 481</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/103/182/tIII/s351/a">Pub. L. 103–182, title III, § 351(a)</ref>, <date date="1993-12-08">Dec. 8, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/2122">107 Stat. 2122</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
